<concept id="concept_mvs_cxf_5z">
 <title>Transport Protocols</title>
 <conbody>
  <p><indexterm>transport protocol<indexterm>default and configuration </indexterm></indexterm>When
            SSL/TLS is enabled in a stage, you can configure the transport protocol to use. </p>
        <p><ph conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/>
            uses <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/TLS-defaultProtocol-ph"
            /> by default. You can specify one or more other protocols, but versions prior to <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/TLS-defaultProtocol-ph"
            /> are not as secure. <draft-comment author="Loretta">Jeff: Is this what we should say?
                Anything else? </draft-comment></p>
 </conbody>
